Package: fasttextM
Type: Package
Title: Fast Multilingual Word Embeddings
Version: 0.2.1
Authors@R: c(person(given = "Taylor B.", family = "Arnold", email = "taylor.arnold@acm.org", role = c("aut", "cre")), person(given = "Nicolas", family = "Bailler", email = "nicolas.ballier@univparis-diderot.fr", role = c("aut")), person(given = "Paula", family = "Liss\'{o}n", email = "paula.lisson@etu.univparis-diderot.fr", role = c("aut")))
Maintainer: Taylor B. Arnold <taylor.arnold@acm.org>
Description: Provides a set of tools for downloading and applying the fasttext word embeddings. All embeddings are fit in-memory for speed. The resulting embeddings can be used for supervised and unsupervised learning over a text-based corpus. Embeddings are consistent across languages, so similar words in different language should get mapped to similar vectors in the output space.
Depends:
    R (>= 2.10)
Imports:
    utils,
    curl (>= 3.0),
    iotools,
    stringi
License: LGPL-2
URL: http://github.com/statsmaths/fasttextM/ 
BugReports: http://github.com/statsmaths/fasttextM/issues
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.0.2
